"n. 窒息 【英】 n. 窒息(loss of consciousness) n. 窒息(因体内氧气减少, 并伴有二氧化碳增多, 而导致失去知觉或死亡的状况) 【根】a非, 无, sphyx脉搏, ia病－没有脉搏的病－窒息as好像, phyx读: fix修理, ia病: 好像是被人修理(卡脖子)过后得的病－窒息 【记】as Phoenix→如同凤凰，埃及神话中的不死鸟,每隔五百年自投火中而死, 又从灰烬中再生→这鸟死时算是进入火堆于浓烟中熏死→窒息；a + sphinx 斯芬克斯，专门掐死（窒息）回答不出谜语的人 asphyxia (n.)  1706, ""stoppage of pulse, absence of pulse,"" from Modern Latin, from Greek asphyxia ""stopping of the pulse,"" from a- ""not"" (see a- (3)) + sphyzein ""to throb."" Obsolete in its original sense; the transferred sense of ""suffocation"" is from 1778, but it is a ""curious infelicity of etymology"" [OED] because victims of suffocation have a pulse for some time after breathing has stopped."
